 Federal Judge Tosses Out Class Action Over Credit Card's Claim of 'Fixed'=
=20
Rate
The Legal Intelligencer
A federal judge in Philadelphia dismissed a claim under the Truth in Lendin=
g=20
Act in a class action suit in which the plaintiff claimed she was falsely=
=20
promised a "fixed" rate of 7.99 percent only to see it raised to 10.5 perce=
nt=20
a year later. The judge found that the TILA has a narrow scope and requires=
=20
only that banks disclose all of the terms that will apply to credit card=20
holders on the day they receive the card.=20
