 Federal Judge Rules for Tribe in New York Tax Dispute
New York Law Journal
Expressing frustration that the judiciary is left to clean up the Indian la=
nd=20
claim mess, a federal judge in New York has barred an upstate city and coun=
ty=20
from collecting property taxes levied against the Oneida Nation. The judge=
=20
held that under the 207-year-old Treaty of Canandaigua, the land at issue i=
n=20
Madison and Oneida counties is "Indian Country" and, as such, is immune fro=
m=20
property taxes.=20
