 3rd Circuit Gives Lessons on Attorneys' Fees
The Legal Intelligencer
Reversing awards of attorneys' fees in two discrimination cases, the 3rd U.=
S.=20
Circuit Court of Appeals is sending a message to trial judges: show your=20
work. The two unpublished opinions are full of important holdings on a=20
variety of thorny issues such as what to do about excessive charges for=20
faxing and copying, and how to calculate hourly fees for lawyers, paralegal=
s=20
and associates.=20
